{"session_id": 49, "bill_id": 15471, "bill_type": "House Bill", "bill_number": 1166, "bill_title": "require minimum training requirements for corrections officers.", "sponsors": [{"legislator_profile_id": 2320, "is_prime": true}, {"legislator_profile_id": 2396, "is_prime": true}, {"legislator_profile_id": 2312, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 2318, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 2334, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 2339, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 2345, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 2348, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 2352, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 2356, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 2358, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 2359, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 2360, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 2362, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 2364, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 2365, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 2368, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 2371, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 2373, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 2378, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 2379, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 2380, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 2382, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 2392, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 2403, "is_prime": false}], "keywords": ["Department of Corrections", "Juvenile Corrections", "Public Employee", "Public Employer"], "audio": [{"meeting_datetime": "2000-02-08T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "H", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2000/hou21hb1166a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2000-02-08T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "H", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2000/hou21hb1166a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2000-02-08T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "H", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2000/hou21hb1166a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2000-02-08T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "H", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2000/hou21hb1166a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}], "bill_versions": [{"bill_id": 15471, "bill_version_id": 86405, "bill_version": "Introduced", "bill_version_date": "2000-01-18T00:00:00-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to require minimum training requirements for corrections officers. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. The Department of Corrections shall develop and conduct a training program based on training approved by a nationally recognized professional association for juvenile correctional officers. The training program shall include: (1) Goals; (2) Objectives; and (3) A curriculum outline which includes adolescent human behavior courses and gender specific human behavior courses. Section 2. The Department of Corrections shall develop and conduct a training program based on training approved by a nationally recognized professional association for adult correctional officers. The training program shall include: (1) Goals; (2) Objectives; and (3) A curriculum outline which includes human behavior courses and gender specific human behavior courses. Section 3. The corrections commission created in \u00a7 1-15-1.13 shall review and approve the training programs created in sections 1 and 2 of this Act by December 31, 2000."}, {"bill_id": 15471, "bill_version_id": 86404, "bill_version": "House State Affairs Engrossed", "bill_version_date": "2000-02-04T00:00:00-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to require minimum training requirements for corrections officers. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That chapter 26-11A be amended by adding thereto a NEW SECTION to read as follows: Any juvenile correctional officer shall complete four hours of instruction regarding domestic abuse and violence. The instruction content shall be approved by the corrections commission established in \u00a7 1-15-1.13. Section 2. That chapter 26-11A be amended by adding thereto a NEW SECTION to read as follows: The Department of Social Services shall reimburse the Department of Corrections for any domestic abuse and violence training as prescribed in section 1 of this Act. The Department of Social Services shall use funding received from the Violence Against Women Act, set out in Title IV of the Violent Crime Control and Law Enforcement Act of 1994. BILL HISTORY 1/19/00 First read in House and referred to committee assignment waived. H.J. 135 1/20/00 Referred to State Affairs. H.J. 160 1/31/00 Scheduled for Committee hearing on this date. 1/31/00 State Affairs Tabled, AYES 7, NAYS 6. H.J. 324 2/3/00 Recalled from committee (Rule 7-7). H.J. 388 2/4/00 State Affairs Hog Housed. 2/4/00 State Affairs Removed from Table, AYES 11, NAYS 1. 2/4/00 State Affairs Do Pass Amended, Passed, AYES 7, NAYS 5. H.J. 427"}], "amendments": [], "fiscal_notes": [], "action_log": [{"bill_id": 15471, "action_date": "2000-01-19T14:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 85632, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/85632.pdf", "status_text": "First read in House and referred to", "journal_page": 135, "committee_id_action": 656, "committee_id_assigned": null, "result": "N", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 15471, "action_date": "2000-01-20T14:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 85634, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/85634.pdf", "status_text": "Referred to", "journal_page": 160, "committee_id_action": 656, "committee_id_assigned": 651, "result": "P", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 15471, "action_date": "2000-01-31T19:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 85823, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/85823.pdf", "status_text": "Scheduled for Committee hearing on this date", "journal_page": null, "committee_id_action": 651, "committee_id_assigned": null, "result": "N", "vote": {}